## How to Add a Page

{% if framework == "astro" %}
1. Create a file in `src/pages/` with a `.astro` or `.md` extension.
2. The file path becomes the URL: `src/pages/about.astro` = `/about`.
3. Every page must import and use a layout from `src/layouts/`.
4. Set SEO frontmatter (`title`, `description`) - see `docs/content-guide.md`.

Example page:

```astro
---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---
<PageLayout title="About" description="About {{ display_name }}.">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>Content here.</p>
</PageLayout>
```

For content-driven pages (blog posts, docs), add a Markdown file to `src/content/` and create the route file in `src/pages/` using `getStaticPaths()`.
{% elif framework == "nextjs-static" %}
1. Create a `.tsx` file in `src/pages/`.
2. The file path becomes the URL: `src/pages/about.tsx` = `/about`.
3. Every page must use a layout from `src/layouts/`.
4. Use `getStaticProps` for any data fetching - no server-side fetching is available in static export mode.
5. Set SEO data using the `<Head>` component from `next/head` or the SEO wrapper in `src/components/seo/`.

For dynamic routes (e.g., blog posts), use `getStaticPaths` to declare all paths.
{% elif framework == "hugo" %}
1. Create a Markdown file in `content/` - the directory structure becomes the URL.
2. Specify a layout with `layout:` frontmatter, or let Hugo choose the layout by type.
3. Set `title` and `description` frontmatter.
4. Use shortcodes from `layouts/shortcodes/` for reusable content snippets.

Hugo's lookup order for layouts: `layouts/{type}/{layout}.html` -> `layouts/_default/single.html`
{% elif framework == "eleventy" %}
1. Create a `.md` or `.njk` file in `src/`.
2. Set the `layout` frontmatter key to a layout file in `src/_includes/layouts/`.
3. Set `title` and `description` frontmatter.
4. The URL is derived from the file path by default; override with `permalink` in frontmatter.

For collection-based pages (blog, etc.), use Eleventy pagination over a collection defined in `.eleventy.js`.
{% endif %}

## Component Patterns

### File Location

| Component type | Location |
|----------------|----------|
| Navigation components | `src/components/navigation/` |
| Content components (callouts, code blocks, embeds) | `src/components/content/` |
| Layout components (header, footer, sidebar) | `src/components/layout/` |
| SEO components (meta tags, structured data) | `src/components/seo/` |

### Naming Conventions

- Component files: PascalCase (`CalloutBlock.astro`, `SiteHeader.astro`)
- One component per file
- Props interface defined at the top of the component

### Styling Components

Approach: **{{ styling }}**

{% if styling == "tailwind" %}
- Use Tailwind utility classes directly in markup
- Extract repeated patterns into component classes with `@apply` in `src/styles/components.css` only when a pattern appears 3+ times
- Do not use arbitrary values (`w-[347px]`) - add a named token to `tailwind.config.mjs` instead
- Responsive breakpoints: `sm:` (640px), `md:` (768px), `lg:` (1024px), `xl:` (1280px)
{% elif styling == "vanilla-css" %}
- Write a dedicated CSS file per component in `src/styles/components/`
- Use custom properties from `src/styles/global.css` for all design tokens - never hardcode colors, spacing, or font sizes
- Use BEM-like class naming: `.component-name`, `.component-name__element`, `.component-name--modifier`
{% elif styling == "scss" %}
- Write a dedicated SCSS partial per component in `src/styles/components/`
- Import the partial in `src/styles/main.scss`
- Use SCSS variables from `src/styles/_tokens.scss` for all design tokens
- Maximum nesting depth: 3 levels
{% endif %}

## Content Patterns

### Adding Content

1. Create a file in the appropriate `src/content/` subdirectory.
2. Include all required frontmatter fields (see `docs/content-guide.md` for the schema per content type).
3. Follow the Markdown style guide in `docs/content-guide.md`.
4. For images: place them alongside the content file (not in `public/`) and use relative paths.

### Content Frontmatter Rules

- `title`: required, 50-60 characters, no trailing period
- `description`: required, 120-160 characters, human-readable sentence
- Never omit required fields - the build will fail with a validation error
{% if site_type == "blog" %}
- `pubDate`: required for blog posts, ISO 8601 format (`YYYY-MM-DD`)
- `draft: true` hides a post from the site and RSS feed - use this for work in progress
{% endif %}
{% if site_type == "docs" %}
- `sidebar.order`: controls the position in the navigation sidebar
{% endif %}

### Images in Content

- Use the framework's image component, never bare `<img>` tags in components
- In Markdown content, use relative paths: `![Alt text](./image.png)`
- Always write meaningful alt text (see `docs/content-guide.md` for guidelines)
- Width and height must be inferrable by the build tool - use source images at actual dimensions

## Styling Conventions

{% if styling == "tailwind" %}
### Tailwind Rules

- Design tokens are in `tailwind.config.mjs` under `theme.extend`
- Color palette uses semantic names (`primary`, `secondary`, `neutral`) not raw color names
- Dark mode uses the `dark:` variant - the theme is toggled via a class on `<html>`
- Typography: use the `@tailwindcss/typography` plugin's `prose` class for long-form content
- Never write inline `style` attributes unless dynamically setting values that cannot be expressed as utilities
{% elif styling == "vanilla-css" %}
### CSS Rules

- All design tokens are custom properties on `:root` in `src/styles/global.css`
- Use `var(--token-name)` everywhere - never hardcode values
- Media queries use the custom property breakpoints: `@media (min-width: var(--breakpoint-md))`
- Color scheme switching: dark mode values are set in `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` and optionally overridden by a `.dark` class
{% elif styling == "scss" %}
### SCSS Rules

- All tokens are in `src/styles/_tokens.scss` as SCSS variables and maps
- Import tokens with `@use '../tokens' as tokens;` in component partials
- Use `tokens.$color-primary` syntax (namespace imports) to avoid pollution
- No `@extend` - use mixins or utility classes instead
{% endif %}

## SEO Metadata Rules

- Every page must have unique `title` and `description` frontmatter
- The base layout automatically generates `<meta>`, Open Graph, and Twitter card tags from these
- OG images default to `public/og-image.png` - override per page with `ogImage:` frontmatter
- The sitemap is generated automatically at build time - no manual sitemap editing

## Deployment Process

Target: **{{ deploy_target }}**

{% if deploy_target == "vercel" %}
- Push to `main` triggers a production deployment automatically
- Every PR branch gets a preview deployment URL (shown in the PR checks)
- Environment variables are managed in the Vercel dashboard (not in code)
- Do not commit `.vercel/` to version control
{% elif deploy_target == "netlify" %}
- Push to `main` triggers a production deployment automatically
- Every PR gets a deploy preview URL (posted as a PR comment)
- Build settings are in `netlify.toml` - do not change them in the Netlify dashboard
- Environment variables are managed in the Netlify dashboard
{% elif deploy_target == "github-pages" %}
- Push to `main` triggers the GitHub Actions workflow in `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`
- The workflow builds the site and pushes output to the `gh-pages` branch
- There is no preview deployment - test locally or use a separate branch deployment
- The site is served from the `gh-pages` branch, not `main`
{% elif deploy_target == "cloudflare-pages" %}
- Push to `main` triggers a production deployment
- Every PR gets a preview deployment URL
- Environment variables are managed in the Cloudflare Pages dashboard
- Do not use Cloudflare-specific APIs unless there is no portable alternative
{% endif %}

